description:
lichen_l2.c lines 674-678:

```c
if (!atomic_get(&link_ctx_initialized)) {
    LOG_WRN("RX before link_ctx initialized - dropping frame");
    k_mutex_unlock(&rx_mutex);
    return;
}
```

The comment at lines 670-673 says 'This shouldn't happen in normal operation' but the log level is WRN. If it truly shouldn't happen, it should arguably be LOG_ERR to make it stand out in logs.

Conversely, if it's a recoverable timing window during startup, the comment should explain when this can legitimately occur and why WRN (not ERR) is appropriate.

What goes wrong: Ambiguity about whether this condition is expected or indicates a bug.

Improvement: Either change to LOG_ERR('BUG: RX before link_ctx initialized') or add to the comment: 'This can occur during early startup if a packet arrives between lichen_lora_l2_start() and lichen_l2_iface_init() completing. The packet is safely dropped.'
